caption:
Attention all tech enthusiasts! Are you ready for the ultimate technological showdown? After tireless planning and preparation, the Students’ Technical Council is thrilled to announce the first edition of TechShila - IIT Roorkee's Inter Bhawan Tech Meet. This exciting event will showcase the best of IITR's extravagant technical culture as Bhawans will compete across various technical domains for securing the General Championship. TechShila 1.0 will be a two-week-long event starting today with a final showdown of participants from 14th to 16th April 2023.

Stay tuned for a set of comprehensive problem statements that are ready to challenge and bring the best out of you! TechShila 1.0 promises to be an exciting learning experience for all participants, providing an opportunity to showcase your technical skills and learn from your fellow competitors.

Represent your Bhawan with pride and elevate your technical skills in this exciting two-week-long event filled with learning opportunities and challenges designed to enhance your tech acumen!

After much anticipation, the Inter IIT Tech Meet 11.0 Low Prep problem statement results are out. We're happy to share that we took home medals in four out of five problem statements.

Gold Medal for Cognitive Garage (Analytics)
Silver Medal for paradime.io (Product Challenge)
Bronze Medal for Saptang Labs (Cyber Security)
Bronze Medal for QuantInsti (Algorithmic Trading)

Also two of our research papers got recognised among best papers in Students' Academic Conference (SAC) and two projects were judged best projects in Engineer's Conclave.

In the General Championship, we have secured the second place. We applaud IIT Roorkee's contingent's dedication and tenacity over the past three months for making this possible. This magnificent achievement is the result of the vibrant tech culture at IITR. Credits to IIT Kanpur's organising committee for the event's successful execution.

The results of Inter IIT Tech Meet 11.0 Mid Prep problem statement are out. We are proud to announce that we have won medals in all four problem statements.

Gold Medal for Consensys (Blockchain)

Bronze Medal for ISRO( CV and Image Processing)

Bronze Medal for Cloudphysician (ML And Healthcare)

Bronze Medal for Jaguar Land Rover (Automotive Engineering)

Stay tuned for the results of Low Prep problem statements!!

Hey freshers!
Hope you all attended the recruitment talk yesterday. The first step towards becoming MaRS core team member is clearing the recruitment test round. The test is scheduled to be conducted on Thursday, 23rd March.
Venue: APJ Abdul Kalam block L2-001
Time: 6:00 pm

Please fill the google form attached below:
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScJJwx-EjPz_h26oRAj01eK3M0XABj9ixYEmn137lDGbf01qA/viewform?usp=sf_link

P.S.: This is a pen-paper based test. You are required to bring your own stationery.
Resources have already been shared on MaRS discord server. You can join us at discord through the following link:
https://discord.gg/RxmwRCXz

You can also access the resources through the MaRS link tree present in the bio.

Best wishes from Team MaRS!

The results of Inter IIT Tech Meet 11.0 High Prep problem statement are out after much anticipation. We are proud to announce that we have won medals in all four problem statements.

Gold Medal for Drona Aviation (Aerial Robotics)

Silver Medal for GradCapital (Tech Entrepreneurship)

Silver Medal for Grow Simplee (ML and Heuristics)

Bronze Medal for Devrev (Natural Language Processing)

Stay tuned for the results of Mid Prep and Low Prep problem statements!!

A huge thanks to the Organising Committee of IIT Kanpur for such smooth conduction of the event.

"The only way to do great work is to love what you do. If you haven’t found it yet, keep looking. Don’t settle."

Starting on this note, ASME IIT Roorkee Student Section is thrilled to invite freshers from various departments to explore their passion.

ASME IIT Roorkee Student Section goes recruiting for the verticals: Design, Web Development, and Content Writing.

Note: Open for 2nd year as well for Web development.

The problem statement for all the verticals can be accessed by QR code and from the link in the bio.

The deadline to submit your solutions is 26 March 2023, 11:59 PM.

For any queries, email us at asmeiitr@iitr.ac.in
Or contact us: 8092794279

For Tech Enthusiasts, we will be recruiting the technical team on March 21, 2023.

All the best:)

Beginner’s hypothesis is now live for freshers along with a small tease of the problem statement for sophomores. Leaderboard position holders will go straight to interviews to be a part of DSG. Good luck!

The much awaited results of Inter IIT Tech Meet 11.0 are finally out. Congratulations to the entire contingent of IIT Roorkee for a splendid performance. We are proud to announce that we have secured 2nd position in the General Championship. This glorious result comes as an outcome of the prolific tech culture of IITR . The commitment and perseverance of our contingent over the last 3 months have paid off and we couldn’t be more proud of their accomplishments . A Huge Thanks to the Organising Committee of IIT Kanpur for such smooth conduction of the event.
Individual results to follow soon!

Do you want to launch your dream app into the market?
Do you want to be the next unicorn in the mobile app industry?

If you’ve answered yes to these questions, then this opportunity is for you.
GreedyGame in collaboration with IIT Roorkee presents “Appicorns 2.0”, a unique mobile app hackathon that aims to support and fund cutting-edge mobile apps that have the potential to create significant end-user value.

You get to walk away with;
A cash prize of 1,00,000 rupees, co-publishing opportunities, internships, industry experts mentorship, public recognition, and more.

Don’t miss out on this incredible opportunity to fulfill your dream. So, take a monumental first step towards achieving your goals by registering for Appicorns 2.0 today!

Visit appicorns.com to learn more.

DSG Recruitments for this session are now LIVE. Missed your shot at BYOP? Don't worry, we got you covered:

1. BYOP- Making end-to-end projects gives you the high, seeing your ideas come to action? Give your all in this month-long code sprint to complete your project, while we are there to pull you out if you get stuck.

2. Beginner's Hypothesis - Kaggle contests seem fun? Make your best submission for the challenge that goes live on 13th March, with different problem Statements for 1y and 2y, and climb your way to the leaderboard. Get your skills sharpened till then, explore through Kaggle and DSG-provided resources.

3. Blog-a-thon: Got conceptual clarity like no one else? If you feel you can intuitively understand algorithms and concepts and can make them explainable to others as well, publish those thoughts in your head and make your thinking astonish us!

Well, we are no professors that can teach you Data Science 0 to 100. So, it only makes it fair if people don't have to go through a test to get in either. There will be NO pen-and-paper test for recruitments, so now only your own efforts can make you come around here. All the best junta, get ready for a time of learning and fun!

Ever wondered what happens in our garage? Ever wanted to come visit us but felt “yaar bohot door hai chhodo”?
Worry not! Because Team IIT Roorkee Motorsports is bridging this gap soon!
Stay Tuned!

Hello Freshers!
Ever wondered how many technical clubs there are on campus? What do they do, and how are they different from each other? The time has finally come for you to catch a glimpse of the technical culture of IITR.
To help you explore our tech clubs, Students' Technical Council IIT Roorkee presents to you Technical Weekend School 2022-23, during which you will get to attend intro talks, workshops, and fun interactive sessions organized by the club members.
Please note that the venue of the sessions will be informed one day prior to the event.

STC is the umbrella organization that consists of institutional and departmental technical groups and is here to promote knowledge among the campus junta and help shape leaders for the future.
